     1  # Worklog ‚Äî Wave 6 `@netscript/cli` A6-v2 promotion
     2  
     3  ## Design
     4  
     5  The CLI is the **last** package in the S1 Package Quality program. 
Research establishes it is a
     6  *fast-evolved A6-v1*, not a broken package: `deno check` clean, zero 
`console.*` leaks, no file >384
     7  LOC, and `src/{kernel,public,maintainer,local}/` already maps to A6's 
kernel-horizontal /
     8  surface-vertical shape. So the promotion to A6-v2 is a **bounded set of 
moves + seam introductions**,
     9  not a rewrite. AP-1 ("Restructure") is valid but its scope is exactly 
the 7-slice plan.
    10  
    11  ### Sequencing rationale
    12  
    13  The CLI deliberately ships **after** everything else (LD-7 / decision 
#7). Phase P publishes all 28
    14  other members to JSR alpha.0 first, which lets slice 4 validate the 
*production* `netscript init`
    15  (JSR-resolved deps) via a new `scaffold.published.runtime` e2e ‚Äî 
closing the single biggest untested
    16  gap (today only the maintainer/local scaffold variants are exercised).
    17  
    18  ### Load-bearing change ‚Äî slice 2
    19  
    20  The typed `CliCommandRegistry` (concrete to Cliffy `Command`, LD-2) 
replacing the hand-wired
    21  `public-command-tree.ts` chain (V-1/F-CLI-27) is the keystone. If slice 
2 doesn't close V-1, the
    22  hand-wired tree becomes a permanent maintenance hotspot (R-15). 
Therefore slice 2 may only merge with
    23  a green `scaffold.runtime` rerun (41/41) ‚Äî enforced by the PR 
template. The `DeployTargetPort` +
    24  `DeployTargetRegistryPort` seam lands in the same slice because it 
removes the `DeployTargetKey`
    25  literal-union lock-in (V-9) and the two changes share the 
command-dispatch surface.
    26  
    27  ### Key design decisions
    28  
    29  1. **Concrete registry, not generic (LD-2).** YAGNI ‚Äî Cliffy `Command`
is the only command runtime;
    30     a generic abstraction adds indirection with no second implementor.
    31  2. **Writers under `maintainer/features/codegen/` (LD-3).** Keeps 
scaffold writers out of `public/`,
    32     satisfying F-CLI-3 (no surface‚Üîsurface import).
    33  3. **Deploy is a port, not a switch.** `DeployTargetPort` + registry; 
`WindowsServiceDeployTarget` is
    34     the one concrete adapter (Windows deploy is *not* Aspire). Future 
k8s/container/cloud adapters wrap
    35     `Aspire.Hosting.{Kubernetes,ContainerApps,AWS,Azure}` ‚Äî seam only, 
no concrete impl this wave.
    36  4. **Single-file ownership with the upgrade run (LD-8).** This wave owns
`scaffold-files.ts` +
    37     `scaffold-aspire.ts` apphost-path migration; the upgrade run owns 
`scaffold-versions.ts` + CI pin.
    38     No file is edited by both programs.
